261
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:20,120
 and there's nothing beautiful.

262
00:10:20,120 --> 00:10:25,600
 And it's in this space that God commissions Zerubbabel.

263
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,520
 I'm gonna read it to you.

264
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:27,440
 He says this.

265
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:30,840
 So the Lord stirred up in the spirit of Zerubbabel,

266
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:33,480
 governor of Judah, and the spirit of Joshua,

267
00:10:33,480 --> 00:10:35,880
 son of Josedach, the high priest,

268
00:10:35,880 --> 00:10:38,120
 and the spirit of the whole remnant of the people.

269
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:40,320
 They came and they began to work

270
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:42,960
 on the house of the Lord Almighty, their God,

271
00:10:42,960 --> 00:10:44,920
 which is found in Haggai.

272
00:10:44,920 --> 00:10:47,240
 So they get back, and everything is a mess.

273
00:10:47,240 --> 00:10:48,320
 There's nothing beautiful.

274
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,080
 It's just rubble, and it's terrible,

275
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,320
 and there's nothing here.

276
00:10:51,320 --> 00:10:54,400
 And God stirs in their spirit.

277
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:58,000
 He initiates it for them.

278
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,000
 Think about this.

279
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:03,720
 God disrupts them and says, "I want you to do this thing.

280
00:11:03,720 --> 00:11:07,440
 "I want you guys to start building my temple again."

281
00:11:07,440 --> 00:11:08,920
 God interrupts their plan.

282
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:10,080
 God intervenes into them.

283
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:12,080
 He stirs their spirit.

284
00:11:12,080 --> 00:11:13,200
 This is good to remember.

285
00:11:13,200 --> 00:11:16,480
 This whole temple thing is God's idea.

286
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:19,080
 Like, it wasn't like they're like,

287
00:11:19,080 --> 00:11:21,320
 "Oh, let's just be really good, and let's build this."

288
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:25,080
 It's like God creates that desire in them,

289
00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:26,520
 and commissions them.

290
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:29,880
 So God's idea given to them, "Go and do this."

291
00:11:29,880 --> 00:11:30,880
 And I think for lots of us,

292
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:33,520
 when we have the idea of God's idea

293
00:11:33,520 --> 00:11:34,680
 sending us to do something,

294
00:11:34,680 --> 00:11:36,800
 or God has led us into this thing,

295
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:39,560
 we carry these preconceived ideas

296
00:11:39,560 --> 00:11:43,320
 that because it's God's idea, it's meant to be easy.

297
00:11:43,320 --> 00:11:45,880
 I mean, I carry that a lot of times.

298
00:11:45,880 --> 00:11:47,840
 I have to regularly, I don't have to do anything.

299
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:50,000
 Actually, just living shows me clearly

300
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:52,200
 that just because I'm following God's plan

301
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,600
 does not mean it's gonna be easy.

302
00:11:54,600 --> 00:11:56,560
 Sometimes I'm like, it becomes harder, right?

303
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:59,120
 Like, sometimes not following God's plan is the easy way,

304
00:11:59,120 --> 00:12:00,240
 and everything is going well,

305
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:01,360
 but then I follow God's plan,

306
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,040
 it's like difficulty, difficulty, difficulty.

307
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,880
 I'm like, "What am I doing?"

308
00:12:04,880 --> 00:12:06,160
 But that's how these people feel.

309
00:12:06,160 --> 00:12:08,480
 The spirit of God stirs in their heart

310
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:11,520
 this desire to build, rebuild the temple.

311
00:12:11,520 --> 00:12:17,200
 He interrupts their life, and sets them on this course.

312
00:12:18,440 --> 00:12:20,440
 And I think their expectation is that,

313
00:12:20,440 --> 00:12:22,640
 okay, if God has commissioned us to do this,

314
00:12:22,640 --> 00:12:25,640
 if he's set it in our hearts, then let's do it.

315
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:26,480
 It's gonna be great.

316
00:12:26,480 --> 00:12:28,120
 And they start to do it.

317
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:29,440
 They expect for it to be easy.

318
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:31,280
 But if you were here a few months back,

319
00:12:31,280 --> 00:12:33,240
 you would've known that we as a Vine community

320
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,880
 went through this series on the book of Ezra,

321
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,680
 looking at this very aspect of the story,

322
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:40,760
 where they go to rebuild, and they get there,

323
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:42,000
 and they're literally standing

324
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:44,440
 in the rubble of the old temple.

325
00:12:44,440 --> 00:12:46,240
 Like, talk about sad.

326
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,680
 Like, you're literally standing in the ruins of it.

327
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:51,240
 And I'm sure there's disappointment, and emotions,

328
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:55,040
 and frustrations, and hurt, and anger, and sadness.

329
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:58,080
 And it's from that space that they're supposed to build.

330
00:12:58,080 --> 00:12:59,640
 And as they start building,

331
00:12:59,640 --> 00:13:02,880
 there's those who are remembering how beautiful,

332
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:05,000
 and how great, and how much splendor

333
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,680
 the old temple used to have.

334
00:13:06,680 --> 00:13:08,080
 The presence of God used to be here.

335
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:10,600
 Solomon, who was the richest king of his day,

336
00:13:10,600 --> 00:13:12,280
 built this magnificent temple.

337
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:15,000
 It was beautiful to look at.

338
00:13:15,000 --> 00:13:16,360
 And here they are standing in rubble,

339
00:13:16,360 --> 00:13:17,200
 trying to rebuild it.

340
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:20,520
 So you have those who are literally weeping.

341
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:23,360
 Then you have those who are worshiping,

342
00:13:23,360 --> 00:13:26,080
 because the idea of building God's temple,

343
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:27,920
 and the presence of God being back with his people,

344
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:29,040
 they could see this future hope.

345
00:13:29,040 --> 00:13:30,600
 So you've got this weeping, and wailing,

346
00:13:30,600 --> 00:13:33,400
 and worshiping happening side by side,

347
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,520
 while standing in the rubble.

348
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:36,680
 And then people start coming against them.

349
00:13:36,680 --> 00:13:38,960
 People start trying to prevent them

350
00:13:38,960 --> 00:13:41,200
 from building the temple.

351
00:13:41,200 --> 00:13:43,080
 So now they're getting more obstacles, and more obstacles.

352
00:13:43,080 --> 00:13:44,960
 And Pastor Andrew took us through a four-week series

353
00:13:44,960 --> 00:13:45,800
 looking at this.

354
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:48,960
 But I wanna take us through what happens after all of that.

355
00:13:48,960 --> 00:13:52,480
 So they go through these obstacles,

356
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:54,200
 and eventually they reach a point where they're like,

357
00:13:54,200 --> 00:13:55,360
 we just can't do it.

358
00:13:55,360 --> 00:13:59,680
 This desire that God had stirred in their hearts

359
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:01,200
 looks impossible.

360
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:02,720
 There's nothing that's making it happen.

361
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:05,640
 Every step there's difficulty, and there's frustration,

362
00:14:05,640 --> 00:14:08,160
 and there's people against us, and situations against us.

363
00:14:08,160 --> 00:14:09,160
 So they quit.

364
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:10,000
 They let it go.

365
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:11,760
 They just let it, they don't disobey God.

366
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:13,160
 They just stop obeying God.

367
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,840
 They let the dream die.

368
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:20,640
 They let it lie dormant for about 20 years.

369
00:14:20,640 --> 00:14:23,800
 And actually, this is a really fascinating story.

370
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:25,080
 I can't go into it here,

371
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:28,000
 but they start building their own lives.

372
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:28,960
 They start rebuilding again.

373
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:31,480
 They've come back to their exiled land,

374
00:14:31,480 --> 00:14:32,320
 where they were exiled from,

375
00:14:32,320 --> 00:14:33,320
 and they're building their lives.

376
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:35,640
 And God's like, you're building your own life,

377
00:14:35,640 --> 00:14:36,480
 but what about the temple?

378
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,440
 But that was too big for them, so they gave up on it.

379
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:40,280
 They let it go for 20 years.

380
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,200
 So they're living in the land,

381
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:45,600
 building up their lives with no temple for 20 years.

382
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:48,200
 And it's in that space that God breaks in

383
00:14:48,200 --> 00:14:51,080
 through the prophet of Zachariah,

384
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:52,320
 speaking to the people,

385
00:14:52,320 --> 00:14:57,280
 giving them perhaps the most important thing

386
00:14:57,280 --> 00:15:00,680
 that they were missing when it came to following God

387
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:02,240
 and building his temple,

388
00:15:02,240 --> 00:15:03,640
 whether it be building his temple

389
00:15:03,640 --> 00:15:06,320
 or just being a follower of Yahweh.

390
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,600
 Some crucial information.

391
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:10,880
 So I'm gonna read for us here in Zachariah chapter four,

392
00:15:10,880 --> 00:15:12,200
 starting at verse one.

393
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:15,840
 This is a vision, so it's not gonna be really clear.

394
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:18,000
 There's gonna be symbols and lamps and trees

395
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:18,840
 and things like that.

396
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:20,600
 But eventually, we'll get to verse six,

397
00:15:20,600 --> 00:15:21,840
 where it'll be super clear.

398
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:24,240
 Says this, "Then the angel who talked with me

399
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:26,080
 "returned and woke me up,

400
00:15:26,080 --> 00:15:28,120
 "like someone awakened from sleep.

401
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,440
 "He asked me, 'What do you see?'

402
00:15:29,440 --> 00:15:31,680
 "And I answered, 'I see a solid gold lampstand

403
00:15:31,680 --> 00:15:34,960
 "'with a bowl at the top and seven lamps on it,

404
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:37,380
 "'with seven channels through the lamps.

405
00:15:37,380 --> 00:15:39,800
 "'Also, there are two olive trees by it,

406
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:42,800
 "'one on the right of the bowl and the other on its left.'

407
00:15:42,800 --> 00:15:44,720
 "I asked the angel who talked to me,

408
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,220
 "'What are these, my Lord?'

409
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:49,520
 "He answered, 'Do you not know what these are?'

410
00:15:49,520 --> 00:15:51,100
 "'No, my Lord,' I replied.

411
00:15:51,100 --> 00:15:52,300
 "So he said to me,

412
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:55,040
 "'This is the word of the Lord to Zerubbabel.

413
00:15:55,040 --> 00:15:58,280
 "'Not by might nor by power,

414
00:15:58,280 --> 00:16:00,880
 "'but by my spirit,' says the Lord Almighty."

415
00:16:00,880 --> 00:16:01,700
 Let me pray.

416
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:06,240
 God, we open your word and we ask, Holy Spirit,

417
00:16:06,240 --> 00:16:09,380
 that you would speak to our hearts.

418
00:16:09,380 --> 00:16:14,120
 That you would come now and give us understanding.

419
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:15,720
 Open our ears.

420
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:18,820
 Allow us to hear what you have to say to us this morning.

421
00:16:18,820 --> 00:16:22,180
 In Jesus' name, amen.

422
00:16:22,180 --> 00:16:25,600
 The picture Zachariah is given

423
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:30,600
 is this picture of these trees and these lampstands.

424
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:33,160
 And there's this oil that's flowing through it.

425
00:16:33,160 --> 00:16:35,380
 The lampstands really don't have a purpose

426
00:16:35,380 --> 00:16:37,000
 if the oil isn't flowing through it.

427
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,720
 So the oil is flowing through it from the trees,

428
00:16:39,720 --> 00:16:42,000
 one on the left and one on the right.

429
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:47,000
 This is God's response to 20 years

430
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:50,440
 of no one working on the thing that he called them to do.

431
00:16:50,440 --> 00:16:53,040
 He gives them a picture of trees and lampstands.

432
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:58,000
 God sees that for 20 years,

433
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,720
 they've struggled so much, they've quit.

434
00:16:59,720 --> 00:17:01,240
 They just let it go.

435
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:05,780
 And his response is trees and lampstand and oil.

436
00:17:05,780 --> 00:17:12,020
 He understood that they felt like they had no way

437
00:17:12,020 --> 00:17:14,500
 to finish what he had commissioned them into.

438
00:17:14,500 --> 00:17:18,860
 He understood that they had obstacles.

439
00:17:18,860 --> 00:17:22,020
 They had run out of strength, out of ability.

440
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:23,460
 And God's response is this,

441
00:17:23,460 --> 00:17:26,000
 that my temple will not be built by might.

442
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,240
 It will not be built by power,

443
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:30,480
 but it will be built by my spirit.

444
00:17:31,420 --> 00:17:34,940
 So what I wanna do today is examine these three elements

445
00:17:34,940 --> 00:17:38,700
 that God speaks on, might and power and spirit.

446
00:17:38,700 --> 00:17:39,940
 Understand what they have in common,

447
00:17:39,940 --> 00:17:41,500
 what's different about them.

448
00:17:41,500 --> 00:17:45,620
 'Cause I think this can be a pretty common Christian verse

449
00:17:45,620 --> 00:17:48,340
 that we might use and hear and be inspired by.

450
00:17:48,340 --> 00:17:50,820
 But I think when we understand its context

451
00:17:50,820 --> 00:17:52,960
 of what it was meant to mean to the people then,

452
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:55,020
 we can better understand how it's meant

453
00:17:55,020 --> 00:17:56,560
 to speak to us today.

454
00:17:58,860 --> 00:18:03,560
 The first word is (speaking in foreign language)

455
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:07,000
 This is the Hebrew word that speaks of strength.

456
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:11,800
 It speaks of power, but it speaks of the individual power,

457
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:15,280
 the individual strength, the individual abilities

458
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:18,600
 and competencies and skills that one might have.

459
00:18:18,600 --> 00:18:21,840
 It's the quality of being able to perform,

460
00:18:21,840 --> 00:18:23,680
 especially a quality that permits

461
00:18:23,680 --> 00:18:25,560
 you're achieving or accomplishing.

462
00:18:25,560 --> 00:18:28,860
 This is how you are able to do something.

463
00:18:28,860 --> 00:18:30,780
 So when God says not by this,

464
00:18:30,780 --> 00:18:33,500
 he's saying not by your physical ability,

465
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:36,580
 not by how resilient you physically are

466
00:18:36,580 --> 00:18:38,540
 or how strong you are mentally,

467
00:18:38,540 --> 00:18:41,520
 not about what you can bring to the table.

468
00:18:41,520 --> 00:18:43,820
 When I read this, I hear God saying,

469
00:18:43,820 --> 00:18:48,040
 promise it's not about your gifts, as good as they are.

470
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:50,260
 It's not about your degrees.

471
00:18:50,260 --> 00:18:54,700
 It's not by your cultural relevance,

472
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:57,340
 which I have done 'cause I'm from America, but you know.

473
00:18:57,340 --> 00:19:00,900
 It's not by the things that you bring to the table.

474
00:19:00,900 --> 00:19:04,120
 That is not how things will get done.

475
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:08,340
 And there's another word that shows up as well.

476
00:19:08,340 --> 00:19:09,620
 (speaking in foreign language)

477
00:19:09,620 --> 00:19:13,460
 This word speaks of wealth, of efficiency,

478
00:19:13,460 --> 00:19:14,900
 of the strength of an army.

479
00:19:14,900 --> 00:19:17,060
 So whereas the first word spoke

480
00:19:17,060 --> 00:19:19,260
 of the individual's competencies,

481
00:19:19,260 --> 00:19:22,300
 this now speaks of the general group,

482
00:19:22,300 --> 00:19:25,220
 the community's efforts, their strength,

483
00:19:25,220 --> 00:19:27,580
 what they, the sum of what all they have,

484
00:19:27,580 --> 00:19:29,300
 what they bring to the table.

485
00:19:29,300 --> 00:19:31,620
 So it's like not by your might promise,

486
00:19:31,620 --> 00:19:34,920
 also not by the vine's efforts, right?

487
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:37,700
 The community, together we're stronger,

488
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:39,820
 but even together we're not enough to get

489
00:19:39,820 --> 00:19:42,140
 to what God is wanting us to get to.

490
00:19:42,140 --> 00:19:47,900
 Which kind of feels discouraging, if I'm honest, right?

491
00:19:47,900 --> 00:19:50,980
 Like the collective resources, is it gonna be enough, God?

492
00:19:50,980 --> 00:19:53,700
 The strength of the nation, the strength of the community.

493
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:55,660
 If we put all of our best foots forward,

494
00:19:55,660 --> 00:19:57,160
 we're still not enough.

495
00:19:57,160 --> 00:19:59,820
 Neither my individual strength or competencies,

496
00:19:59,820 --> 00:20:02,940
 nor our collective efforts will be enough.

497
00:20:02,940 --> 00:20:04,220
 The question that comes to mind is,

498
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:06,940
 has God called us to things that we can't accomplish?

499
00:20:06,940 --> 00:20:12,660
 I feel like that's not really a good church question, is it?

500
00:20:12,660 --> 00:20:15,780
 But I think it's one we have to wrestle with,

501
00:20:15,780 --> 00:20:17,420
 because I think there's something

502
00:20:17,420 --> 00:20:19,620
 for us to understand in this.

503
00:20:19,620 --> 00:20:22,020
 Has God led us to these visions,

504
00:20:22,020 --> 00:20:24,260
 and to these directions, and to these steps

505
00:20:24,260 --> 00:20:26,340
 that actually we can't do?

506
00:20:26,340 --> 00:20:28,980
 And if he has, why?

507
00:20:28,980 --> 00:20:31,260
 What exactly is the purpose of having a start

508
00:20:31,260 --> 00:20:32,380
 if we can't finish?

509
00:20:32,380 --> 00:20:33,700
 If we don't have the strength,

510
00:20:33,700 --> 00:20:34,940
 if we don't have the resources,

511
00:20:34,940 --> 00:20:36,180
 if we don't have the network,

512
00:20:36,180 --> 00:20:37,660
 if we don't have all the things that we need,

513
00:20:37,660 --> 00:20:40,740
 if we don't have, if by our might and by our power,

514
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:43,540
 it's not gonna be enough to accomplish what you're doing,

515
00:20:43,540 --> 00:20:45,100
 then why?

516
00:20:47,980 --> 00:20:52,460
 Why does God start this response of his people

517
00:20:52,460 --> 00:20:54,540
 by telling them what will not work first?

518
00:20:54,540 --> 00:20:56,620
 It's rather than telling them, "Do this,"

519
00:20:56,620 --> 00:20:59,580
 he says, "Don't do this, don't do this."

520
00:20:59,580 --> 00:21:01,820
 I love the order in which he's said.

521
00:21:01,820 --> 00:21:06,500
 He starts by addressing the things

522
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:08,740
 that we tend to put our trust in.

523
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:10,380
 So we as human beings, naturally,

524
00:21:10,380 --> 00:21:12,180
 we're going to trust what we know works.

525
00:21:12,180 --> 00:21:14,780
 And in so many cases, having the right resources,

526
00:21:14,780 --> 00:21:17,620
 knowing the right people, having the right degrees,

527
00:21:17,620 --> 00:21:19,820
 this is how we normally get by in life, right?

528
00:21:19,820 --> 00:21:20,940
 Like, did you go to the right school?

529
00:21:20,940 --> 00:21:22,220
 Did you have the right internship?

530
00:21:22,220 --> 00:21:23,060
 Do you know the right people?

531
00:21:23,060 --> 00:21:24,340
 Did you rub shoulders with whoever?

532
00:21:24,340 --> 00:21:25,180
 Do you have enough money?

533
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:26,220
 Do you live in this right place?

534
00:21:26,220 --> 00:21:28,140
 Then you can achieve X, Y, and Z.

535
00:21:28,140 --> 00:21:30,460
 That's the metric that we normally live in.

536
00:21:30,460 --> 00:21:32,780
 And God's like, "Actually, that's irrelevant.

537
00:21:32,780 --> 00:21:35,300
 "It doesn't matter."

538
00:21:35,300 --> 00:21:38,660
 He starts by telling us that we don't need

539
00:21:38,660 --> 00:21:41,060
 to trust those things.

540
00:21:41,060 --> 00:21:43,780
 We don't need to rely on those things.

541
00:21:43,780 --> 00:21:45,220
 Let's understand this.

542
00:21:45,220 --> 00:21:48,460
 God is saying they're irrelevant in accomplishing

543
00:21:48,460 --> 00:21:50,020
 His goals if we depend on them.

544
00:21:50,020 --> 00:21:51,620
 He's not saying that we can't have them.

545
00:21:51,620 --> 00:21:53,660
 So God's not saying, "Give up all your resources,

546
00:21:53,660 --> 00:21:55,860
 "give up all your strength, just completely be limp."

547
00:21:55,860 --> 00:21:58,020
 That's not the Bible.

548
00:21:58,020 --> 00:22:00,740
 However, what we rely on versus what we have

549
00:22:00,740 --> 00:22:02,020
 are two different things.

550
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:07,300
 We as people, the temptation is to put our trust

551
00:22:07,300 --> 00:22:08,660
 in these things.

552
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:10,740
 And God is saying this, that all those things,

553
00:22:10,740 --> 00:22:14,420
 might and power and strength and things you can accumulate

554
00:22:14,420 --> 00:22:17,020
 and all the things that you have,

555
00:22:17,020 --> 00:22:19,140
 they make pretty crummy gods.

556
00:22:19,140 --> 00:22:24,820
 They aren't meant to be depended on.

557
00:22:24,820 --> 00:22:28,900
 They're not meant to be relied on.

558
00:22:28,900 --> 00:22:35,660
 It's not by them that you accomplish the things of God.

559
00:22:35,660 --> 00:22:40,100
 So you use your resources, use your strength,

560
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:45,100
 use your wealth, but rely on, depend on and trust in God.

561
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:51,180
 This is the course correction He's making.

562
00:22:51,180 --> 00:22:52,460
 It's not saying one is bad, one is good.

563
00:22:52,460 --> 00:22:56,100
 He's saying only one of these can be relied on.

564
00:22:56,100 --> 00:22:59,620
 Only one of these is big enough for you to depend on,

565
00:22:59,620 --> 00:23:02,700
 for you to put your faith and your trust in.

566
00:23:02,700 --> 00:23:07,140
 When we start to trust and depend on our resources,

567
00:23:07,140 --> 00:23:08,300
 what ends up happening?

568
00:23:08,860 --> 00:23:10,340
 I found this very profound for me.

569
00:23:10,340 --> 00:23:11,180
 It may not be profound for you,

570
00:23:11,180 --> 00:23:14,180
 but as I was studying this, it really wrestled with my head.

571
00:23:14,180 --> 00:23:16,780
 When we start to depend on our resources

572
00:23:16,780 --> 00:23:18,740
 and the things that we have, by nature,

573
00:23:18,740 --> 00:23:21,820
 we then start to determine what is possible

574
00:23:21,820 --> 00:23:23,180
 based off of what we have.

575
00:23:23,180 --> 00:23:27,060
 If I have enough of this, I can go this far.

576
00:23:27,060 --> 00:23:29,580
 If I've accumulated this, I can now do this.

577
00:23:29,580 --> 00:23:32,620
 It doesn't work for God.

578
00:23:32,620 --> 00:23:36,060
 You can't use your resources and your might

579
00:23:36,060 --> 00:23:38,420
 and your strength to determine

580
00:23:38,420 --> 00:23:39,820
 if God wants you to go somewhere.

581
00:23:39,820 --> 00:23:41,380
 What happens if God calls you to go somewhere

582
00:23:41,380 --> 00:23:42,940
 and you don't have the resources?

583
00:23:42,940 --> 00:23:44,420
 Must not be God.

584
00:23:44,420 --> 00:23:46,780
 Ooh, but we have so many stories

585
00:23:46,780 --> 00:23:49,340
 of God just saying, "Get up, Abraham, and go."

586
00:23:49,340 --> 00:23:52,220
 Where's he going?

587
00:23:52,220 --> 00:23:53,060
 I don't know.

588
00:23:53,060 --> 00:23:55,180
 Leave everything behind.

589
00:23:55,180 --> 00:23:57,540
 To disciples, just forget about mother and father,

590
00:23:57,540 --> 00:23:59,820
 forget about being a dad, forget about fixing your cattle,

591
00:23:59,820 --> 00:24:02,140
 forget about your farm, come and follow me.

592
00:24:02,140 --> 00:24:05,020
 He says, "Forget about Abraham,

593
00:24:05,020 --> 00:24:07,860
 "forget about the stuff."

594
00:24:07,860 --> 00:24:10,740
 So we don't determine if God has called us into a season.

595
00:24:10,740 --> 00:24:13,500
 We don't determine if we should stay and fight

596
00:24:13,500 --> 00:24:15,140
 based off of what we have.

597
00:24:15,140 --> 00:24:17,300
 We determine if we should stay in it

598
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:19,700
 based off of who we have.

599
00:24:19,700 --> 00:24:22,420
 And who do we have?

600
00:24:22,420 --> 00:24:26,060
 Who has been given to us?

601
00:24:26,060 --> 00:24:29,060
 It's not by might, it's not by power,

602
00:24:29,060 --> 00:24:34,060
 but it's by the Spirit, by my Spirit.

603
00:24:34,060 --> 00:24:36,860
 (audience member coughs)

604
00:24:36,860 --> 00:24:40,180
 I was, I don't know why I keep sharing this detail.

605
00:24:40,180 --> 00:24:45,180
 So when I connect with God and I hear him speak,

606
00:24:45,180 --> 00:24:47,860
 there's a place in my house that it happens at most.

607
00:24:47,860 --> 00:24:49,900
 That place happens to be in the shower.

608
00:24:49,900 --> 00:24:52,580
 I don't know why, but God just likes to talk a lot

609
00:24:52,580 --> 00:24:54,700
 when I have really hot water running on my body.

610
00:24:54,700 --> 00:24:57,740
 So last night, I'm getting ready, I'm praying,

611
00:24:57,740 --> 00:25:00,460
 and I'm taking a shower, and God starts like,

612
00:25:00,460 --> 00:25:02,340
 I don't know, just kind of like downloading some things

613
00:25:02,340 --> 00:25:03,580
 that I didn't write into my sermon.

614
00:25:03,580 --> 00:25:05,180
 So this is off-script production.

615
00:25:05,180 --> 00:25:09,380
 But he was giving me this clear picture

616
00:25:09,380 --> 00:25:13,540
 of the difference that separates

617
00:25:13,540 --> 00:25:17,340
 might, power, and Spirit of God.

618
00:25:17,340 --> 00:25:19,580
 So when it comes to might and power,

619
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:23,060
 those things naturally put you in a posture of taking.

620
00:25:23,060 --> 00:25:24,820
 With your might, you can achieve these things.

621
00:25:24,820 --> 00:25:25,980
 You can reach these things.

622
00:25:25,980 --> 00:25:28,580
 With your power, you can get this, you can grab this,

623
00:25:28,580 --> 00:25:31,220
 you can achieve, you can take for yourself.

624
00:25:32,820 --> 00:25:34,620
 The Spirit of God cannot be taken.

625
00:25:34,620 --> 00:25:39,300
 Small detail, but the Spirit of God cannot,

626
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:42,700
 you can't might enough to get the Spirit of God

627
00:25:42,700 --> 00:25:43,980
 or the gifts of God.

628
00:25:43,980 --> 00:25:47,820
 They are received, they are bestowed upon us.

629
00:25:47,820 --> 00:25:51,100
 And the posture that we carry will determine

630
00:25:51,100 --> 00:25:53,140
 which of those things that we're doing.

631
00:25:53,140 --> 00:25:55,540
 Are we trying to get to the things of God

632
00:25:55,540 --> 00:25:58,380
 by taking and reaching and aiming and striving,

633
00:25:58,380 --> 00:26:00,900
 or have we postured ourselves enough

634
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:04,100
 to receive strength from Him,

635
00:26:04,100 --> 00:26:06,700
 to receive the gifts that He gives

636
00:26:06,700 --> 00:26:09,500
 that helps us to accomplish the things that He wants,

637
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:11,540
 even the endurance to withstand

638
00:26:11,540 --> 00:26:15,060
 the years upon years of having to wait?

639
00:26:15,060 --> 00:26:22,820
 Is our posture receiving, or is our posture taking?

640
00:26:22,820 --> 00:26:25,220
 Is our posture by might and power and strength,

641
00:26:25,220 --> 00:26:28,860
 or is it by receiving what the Spirit has for us?

642
00:26:28,860 --> 00:26:31,740
 He says, "By my Spirit."

643
00:26:31,740 --> 00:26:34,780
 It's one of the things that I love that God doesn't do here.

644
00:26:34,780 --> 00:26:36,220
 I love it, but I hate it at the same time,

645
00:26:36,220 --> 00:26:37,380
 so I'm kind of torn about it.

646
00:26:37,380 --> 00:26:40,500
 He doesn't promise that the obstacles are gonna go away.

647
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:43,620
 Like, I would really love if this verse was like,

648
00:26:43,620 --> 00:26:45,700
 "Not by power, not by might,

649
00:26:45,700 --> 00:26:48,220
 "all the problems are gonna go away because of my Spirit."

650
00:26:48,220 --> 00:26:50,060
 Like, I don't have tattoos, but that would be one

651
00:26:50,060 --> 00:26:52,020
 that I would put on my body immediately.

652
00:26:52,020 --> 00:26:53,540
 Right, like, if He just promised

653
00:26:53,540 --> 00:26:56,180
 that all the problems are gonna go away, He doesn't.

654
00:26:57,820 --> 00:27:02,220
 By my Spirit, but the obstacles are still gonna come.

655
00:27:02,220 --> 00:27:04,940
 I think it's a bit of a reality check for us sometimes,

656
00:27:04,940 --> 00:27:06,300
 that even with the Spirit of God,

657
00:27:06,300 --> 00:27:09,780
 you will still face tribulations.

658
00:27:09,780 --> 00:27:11,780
 You will still face obstacles.

659
00:27:11,780 --> 00:27:14,540
 You will still face resistance

660
00:27:14,540 --> 00:27:18,340
 in the very thing that God has called you into.

661
00:27:18,340 --> 00:27:20,740
 And how do we make it through that?

662
00:27:20,740 --> 00:27:23,700
 And it won't be by our might.

663
00:27:23,700 --> 00:27:25,780
 It won't be by what we have.

664
00:27:25,780 --> 00:27:28,980
 It won't be by our collective strength.

665
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:32,980
 It will be by His power, by His Spirit.

666
00:27:32,980 --> 00:27:36,620
 To an extent, He says might and power are irrelevant

667
00:27:36,620 --> 00:27:39,580
 when compared to the Spirit of God,

668
00:27:39,580 --> 00:27:41,140
 which might sound kind of crazy to say,

669
00:27:41,140 --> 00:27:44,860
 but there's exponentially greater value

670
00:27:44,860 --> 00:27:48,060
 in the confidence of the Spirit with us

671
00:27:48,060 --> 00:27:50,760
 than having all the resources we think we need.

672
00:27:50,760 --> 00:27:54,660
 If you know the Spirit,

673
00:27:54,660 --> 00:27:56,420
 you know this statement to be true.

674
00:27:56,420 --> 00:28:01,220
 During the 9/15, end of the 9/15,

675
00:28:01,220 --> 00:28:03,100
 I was talking with somebody and it hit me again.

676
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:05,060
 I'm like, I kind of wish God would tell me

677
00:28:05,060 --> 00:28:06,900
 all these things beforehand so I could write them all

678
00:28:06,900 --> 00:28:08,580
 into the sermon and it could flow pretty,

679
00:28:08,580 --> 00:28:10,580
 but He doesn't, He just kind of tells me randomly.

680
00:28:10,580 --> 00:28:11,580
 So another thought came to mind,

681
00:28:11,580 --> 00:28:13,100
 so I thought I'd share it with you guys as well.

682
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:15,340
 Might and power and strength,

683
00:28:15,340 --> 00:28:19,500
 all of those are finite resources.

684
00:28:19,500 --> 00:28:23,260
 Resources end.

685
00:28:23,260 --> 00:28:24,460
 They don't go on forever.

686
00:28:24,460 --> 00:28:26,900
 Like half of our world is in so much chaos

687
00:28:26,900 --> 00:28:28,660
 because we're fighting for resources.

688
00:28:28,660 --> 00:28:31,180
 We're using our might and our power to hoard these things.

689
00:28:31,180 --> 00:28:34,500
 The Spirit of God, that picture of the olive tree

690
00:28:34,500 --> 00:28:37,140
 and the olive oil just overflowing,

691
00:28:37,140 --> 00:28:39,900
 there is no end to Him.

692
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:44,140
 He's the beginning and He's the end.

693
00:28:44,140 --> 00:28:48,660
 What He can do with or without our resources

694
00:28:48,660 --> 00:28:50,580
 is abundantly bigger than anything

695
00:28:50,580 --> 00:28:53,260
 that we could accommodate for ourselves.

696
00:28:53,260 --> 00:28:54,860
 I'm saying all this just to say,

697
00:28:54,860 --> 00:28:59,300
 don't count God out because you don't have

698
00:28:59,300 --> 00:29:02,260
 the stuff you need to keep following Him.

699
00:29:02,260 --> 00:29:05,820
 Don't count Him out because the job doesn't pay well enough

700
00:29:05,820 --> 00:29:09,180
 or you don't know the language of the city

701
00:29:09,180 --> 00:29:10,020
 that you're moving to.

702
00:29:10,020 --> 00:29:11,580
 That sounds crazy.

703
00:29:11,580 --> 00:29:13,300
 Like I moved to Hong Kong, I've shared it too many times,

704
00:29:13,300 --> 00:29:14,860
 I won't go into details, but I came here

705
00:29:14,860 --> 00:29:15,900
 only knowing about rush hour.

706
00:29:15,900 --> 00:29:17,220
 I knew nothing about this city

707
00:29:17,220 --> 00:29:19,180
 and I've been here for 12 years now.

708
00:29:19,180 --> 00:29:20,580
 Like don't count God out

709
00:29:20,580 --> 00:29:22,980
 because you don't have the resources.

710
00:29:22,980 --> 00:29:24,740
 Don't count God out because you don't have

711
00:29:24,740 --> 00:29:26,900
 the physical strength or the ability

712
00:29:26,900 --> 00:29:28,660
 or the skill set or the networking

713
00:29:28,660 --> 00:29:30,540
 or the you name the thing.

714
00:29:30,540 --> 00:29:36,900
 No, we don't determine His calling

715
00:29:36,900 --> 00:29:39,660
 and His desire for us to endure

716
00:29:39,660 --> 00:29:43,620
 based off of what we have, but it's by His Spirit.

717
00:29:43,620 --> 00:29:46,740
 That's the key to this whole thing.

718
00:29:46,740 --> 00:29:50,100
 You think about how Jesus would call His disciples,

719
00:29:50,100 --> 00:29:53,420
 follow me, gave them nothing, just said follow me.

720
00:29:53,420 --> 00:29:54,740
 Think about if you've been here at the Vine

721
00:29:54,740 --> 00:29:57,260
 for the past year, the one word that has been

722
00:29:57,260 --> 00:30:00,100
 in like every sermon series is uncharted, right?

723
00:30:00,100 --> 00:30:02,300
 This uncharted territories, uncharted waters,

724
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:03,540
 uncharted everything.

725
00:30:03,540 --> 00:30:05,540
 This idea that God is calling us into a space

726
00:30:05,540 --> 00:30:07,580
 that we do not know as a community.

727
00:30:07,580 --> 00:30:09,900
 A space where our maps and our navigational tools

728
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:11,980
 aren't gonna be able to help us.

729
00:30:11,980 --> 00:30:15,660
 Where our resources aren't gonna be able to be relied upon.

730
00:30:15,660 --> 00:30:17,300
 Where we're not gonna have a strategy

731
00:30:17,300 --> 00:30:19,380
 that we can fall back on.

732
00:30:20,220 --> 00:30:24,180
 But instead we're gonna have to trust in Him.

733
00:30:24,180 --> 00:30:26,700
 Which is a terrifying yet liberating thing.

734
00:30:26,700 --> 00:30:28,940
 So let me reframe the slightly controversial question

735
00:30:28,940 --> 00:30:30,420
 I asked earlier and put it this way.

736
00:30:30,420 --> 00:30:33,380
 Has God called us into things bigger

737
00:30:33,380 --> 00:30:35,780
 than we ourselves could accomplish?

738
00:30:35,780 --> 00:30:37,780
 See it's a little bit different

739
00:30:37,780 --> 00:30:39,780
 when you look at it that way.

740
00:30:39,780 --> 00:30:42,540
 It's more about what He wants to do

741
00:30:42,540 --> 00:30:45,060
 and less about how able we are.

742
00:30:45,060 --> 00:30:48,060
 Which is the predominant posture we should carry

743
00:30:48,060 --> 00:30:50,340
 into this new year.

744
00:30:50,340 --> 00:30:52,100
 If God is calling you to endure a thing,

745
00:30:52,100 --> 00:30:56,420
 if He's calling you to stay in a moment, to continue,

746
00:30:56,420 --> 00:31:00,420
 it's less about your ability and so much more

747
00:31:00,420 --> 00:31:03,260
 about what He is able to do.

748
00:31:03,260 --> 00:31:12,220
 I'm gonna skip ahead production.

749
00:31:12,220 --> 00:31:17,060
 I read this and I think, take the pressure off.

750
00:31:18,060 --> 00:31:20,540
 It's up to God to accomplish what's gonna happen.

751
00:31:20,540 --> 00:31:23,060
 You can breathe.

752
00:31:23,060 --> 00:31:26,260
 I mean I know it's hard, but we can breathe.

753
00:31:26,260 --> 00:31:27,420
 It's not up to us.

754
00:31:27,420 --> 00:31:29,860
 We were never strong enough to begin with.

755
00:31:29,860 --> 00:31:33,180
 We've always needed Him.

756
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:39,780
 So allow that breath to give you strength again.

757
00:31:39,780 --> 00:31:40,980
 God's got it.

758
00:31:40,980 --> 00:31:42,860
 I think this is why Paul can say things like

759
00:31:42,860 --> 00:31:45,660
 in 2 Corinthians that God's strength

760
00:31:45,660 --> 00:31:48,220
 is made perfect in our weakness.

761
00:31:48,220 --> 00:31:50,500
 Now it doesn't matter how strong I am,

762
00:31:50,500 --> 00:31:54,420
 but I boast in my weakness because I know who is strong

763
00:31:54,420 --> 00:31:55,780
 and I know who is with me.

764
00:31:55,780 --> 00:31:57,420
 So if I don't have the ability,

765
00:31:57,420 --> 00:31:59,620
 but the God of the universe now resides,

766
00:31:59,620 --> 00:32:03,700
 His presence, His temple, His dwelling place is inside of me

767
00:32:03,700 --> 00:32:07,180
 then technically I can do all things through Christ

768
00:32:07,180 --> 00:32:08,740
 who strengthens me.

769
00:32:08,740 --> 00:32:09,860
 Amen?

770
00:32:09,860 --> 00:32:12,180
 Because of He who is in us.

771
00:32:12,180 --> 00:32:13,940
 Greater, so many scriptures come to mind.

772
00:32:13,940 --> 00:32:16,340
 But greater is He who is in us

773
00:32:16,340 --> 00:32:18,420
 than He who is in the obstacle that's coming.

774
00:32:18,420 --> 00:32:20,380
 Greater is He who is in us

775
00:32:20,380 --> 00:32:22,860
 than He who is in the waiting for years upon years.

776
00:32:22,860 --> 00:32:26,220
 Greater is He who is within us

777
00:32:26,220 --> 00:32:27,700
 than He who is within the world.

778
00:32:27,700 --> 00:32:31,580
 Guys, we've got something great inside of us.

779
00:32:31,580 --> 00:32:33,500
 The Holy Spirit.

780
00:32:33,500 --> 00:32:35,780
 I just wish, like I can't fully comprehend it,

781
00:32:35,780 --> 00:32:37,980
 but I wish we could all comprehend it more.

782
00:32:37,980 --> 00:32:41,700
 That the God of the universe, His spirit, His essence,

783
00:32:41,700 --> 00:32:44,260
 the power by which He says

784
00:32:44,260 --> 00:32:45,860
 that we would be able to do greater things

785
